    "AIS frameworks aim to provide a numerical approximation of some particular moment of x:where f ∶ → ℝ can be any function of x integrable with respect to the pdf π (x)The integral I(f) is representative of different mathemati- cal problems, from Bayesian inference [113] to the estimate of rare events [48].",
